featured_reviews.review_text: Here, the taste of the Korean food is not bad. The restaurant is owned by a Korean owner, and the staff also speak Korean. The environment is very creative, when eating inside, it feels like eating on the streets of Seoul with orange pojangmacha.

Probably the only tteokbokki specialty restaurant in Singapore, and it’s a pretty solid option to satisfy your carb cravings!

What I tried:
❤️ Mini Plain (added cheese)
This came with glass noodles, half a fully boiled egg, noodle tteok, one fried mandu, vegetables and a fried fish cake. Surprisingly does not come with cylinder tteok which you have to add on, but I did throughly enjoy the noodle shaped rice cakes, which were soft and super chewy! It was very delicious and satisfied my tteokbokki cravings. You can add on other ingredients or types of rice cakes (like sweet potato tteok!) I recommend adding sliced cheese 🧀 hehe. The fried fish cake was really tasty and had the perfect crunchy yet chewy texture 🫨🥹👌👍 Really liked it!!

❤️ Mul Naengmyeon
The arrowhead noodles were thin, super cold and chilly, with nice tangy flavour. Pretty good!

The place is really cozy and feels like you’re in a pojangmacha in korea! Definitely a fun experience and atmosphere.
Overall, would recommend their tteokbokki! I want to try their croffles and tteokbokki hotpot next time..

food 5/5
service 5/5 (food served quickly, nice and hot!)
ambience 5/5

Casual but delicious tteokpoki place. I recommend taking the small portion (from lunch menu) in order to have also other snacks. I loved the plain tteokpoki and the corn cheese (cheese dog). The lady taking care of the service was very lovely and everything was reasonably priced.

Soju is quite cheap there so can be a good place for boozy dinner with friends.

Red Holic : Tanjog Pagar : Singapore (Photo)

'Yes Place ! Supercomfortable ! People !
Korean Touches ?! yes Woman Power !
vegetarian like me Bibimbab is so gooooood :)
Indian like me Tteokbokki + Jabchae-Mandu + Jumeokbab + Spicy Tteokbokki Powder sooo fiyaaa
water can be foul but yeah 'Red Holic' challenges completed :)'

88 Tg Pagar Rd, Singapore 088509

Authentic and delicious! Great service by the owner. We felt like we were being transported to Seoul! Perfect and will definitely visit again to try all the food in the menu! Especially Gimbap is the best🤤

this place was generally okay. cheese fall is a must-get if you're there, otherwise the food tastes mostly like any other army stews / dakgalbi. found the sauce a bit too sweet for my liking. cheese fall added a lot of flavours to the chicken, albeit a little steep in pricing ($8.90 per fall). also got the sides but tastes pretty normal as well.

the rice cakes however, were pretty good - unlike some which are too hard or too mushy, the rice cakes here were done nicely, and with a variety as well.

do note that they don't serve water or side dishes here, unlike other korean food joints.

Recommended for the tteokbokki
They really serve good tteokbokki.. first try and love it.. if you like tteokbokki this restaurant can try..won’t regret
Good food and good service
Also got CASS 😍😍😍

Oreo croffle tasted amazing! One of the best croffle in Singapore. Freshly made and crispy (Might take awhile though). Definitely would recommend if you are looking for a Korean grade croffle, 👍👍👍 Ordered Green Grape Ade is really refreshing :)

detailed_reviews.review_text: One and only authentic tteokbokki place in Singapore! Remember to order cheese to enjoy the real Korean tteokbokki with pork cutlet. The owner is friendly and caters to the needs of the customers too!
Satisfied my crazy random craving for tteokbokki & fish cake soup + more! The croffle is super yummy. Highly recommend!!
Recommended for the tteokbokki They really serve good tteokbokki.. first try and love it.. if you like tteokbokki this restaurant can try..won t regret Good food and good service Also got CASS
Nice place, comfortable and pleasant environment. Staffs were friendly and nice. Definitely will come back again.
10 of 10 for their injeolmi croffle
Staff are super friendly , always make sure customer are satisfied and pricing are affordable too
Staff are super friendly , always make sure that were having our best time dining in. Food are fast and affordable
This is my second visit. The tteokbokki is really delicious and the owner is very kind..       The portion size is great Next time I will come again to eat rose tteokbokki

Here, the taste of the Korean food is not bad. The restaurant is owned by a Korean owner, and the staff also speak Korean. The environment is very creative, when eating inside, it feels like eating on the streets of Seoul with orange pojangmacha.

I m a bit disappointed that they removed their old menu.. now they just serve normal tteokbokki and you need to add on the meat of choice with the increase in price. However the service given is still good and standard of phone is still there.
$18 for this Jjajang noodle?? Looks more like instant mee Goreng and a badly fried sunny side up.

Casual but delicious tteokpoki place. I recommend taking the small portion (from lunch menu) in order to have also other snacks. I loved the plain tteokpoki and the corn cheese (cheese dog). The lady taking care of the service was very lovely and everything was reasonably priced. Soju is quite cheap there so can be a good place for boozy dinner with friends.

Whoever likes spicy food, do drop by Redholic at Tanjong Pagar. They are serving varieties of tteokbokki. Spicyness level can be choose based on your preference. If you are a soju lover, tteokbokki is the best choice to go with. Strongly recommended.

Surprisingly does not come with cylinder tteok which you have to add on, but I did throughly enjoy the noodle shaped rice cakes, which were soft and super chewy! It was very delicious and satisfied my tteokbokki cravings. You can add on other ingredients or types of rice cakes (like sweet potato tteok!) I recommend adding sliced cheese   hehe. I want to try their croffles and tteokbokki hotpot next time.. food 5/5 service 5/5 (food served quickly, nice and hot!) ambience 5/5

Red Holic : Tanjog Pagar : Singapore (Photo) Yes Place ! Supercomfortable ! People ! Korean Touches ?! yes Woman Power ! vegetarian like me Bibimbab is so gooooood :) Indian like me Tteokbokki + Jabchae-Mandu + Jumeokbab + Spicy Tteokbokki Powder sooo fiyaaa water can be foul but yeah Red Holic challenges completed :) 88 Tg Pagar Rd, Singapore 088509

I ordered mango shaved ice and it was topped with a ton of mango sashimi!! Its my first time seeing a mango that looks like this... Fresh mango and a very delicious milk shaved ice inside    Impressive... The addition of the sweet syrup you prepared is the icing on the cake. I highly recommend it as a dessert.
Food here is recommended indeed, additionally the service given was exceptional. Nice atmosphere and not so close to no waiting time.
One of the best Korean street food that Ive had here, reminds me of Korea! Staff were friendly as well, cozy interior. Will definitely be back again soon!!

I went to eat spicy spicy tteokbokki and discovered a new world. The ultimate in superficiality, Crople! I was only going to eat one, but I ended up adding one more. Coffee thats just my taste, what about bear ice! Einspenner coffee, a favorite whipped cream that is pleasing to the eyes and mouth. Mango shaved ice generously topped with a whole mango and a cute duck sitting on it. While I was eating Mala Tteokppok, I took a bite of my daughters mango shaved ice and it was a great combination!!! The classic shaved ice, my unchanging love, red bean shaved ice. A taro latte with a very beautiful color, perfect for my daughter who loves pretty coffee. A cool, clean, small store. Deliciously prepared snacks and desserts that are now the most popular in Korea. Very kind and considerate, pretty owner. You must eat it every time you pass by Tanpa! Kid-friendliness: Kids favorite menu Fish cake soup, tteokbokki, rice balls, water dumplings, pork cutlet Marshmallow crople, mango shaved ice, taro latte
Redholic food,i like spicy ricecake very yummy,,and fishcake soup,,korean food very amazing iloveit

Everyone, foreign workers in Singapore!! Travelers!! Singaporeans!!! Come to Redholic right now.. Its already been n months since I lived in Singapore.. I finally found the taste of Korea in Singapore.. I literally sang the 5th verse of the national anthem as soon as I took a bite.. Its so, so delicious... Youre crazy. The owner provides service. Please give me your life and I can die here. I will come again. Boss, please absolutely protect this place for the rest of my life..
Feels like real korea pocha deep inside. Nice rose rice cake stew too.
food was mid
I have been to Korea once, and this place has definitely made me reminisce over those fond memories. Definitely a place to visit!!
Great vibes and food. Staff were friendly and had a warm atmosphere.
food and staff were the most amazing i felt like i was at home when at this restaurant, the food made me feel like i was at the ends of the world, delighted with every bite!!
If you want to feel the taste of Korean instant tteokbokki, this is the best choice. There are many other menu items and the owner is really friendly!

The aunt was kind, but the food was all average. Two of us ordered Signature plain Tteokbbokki and cheese fall, but the taste was a bit sweet and we got bored. It might be good for people who like cheese, but the beef and cabbage also tasted a little weird.

We got the army stew, corndogs, and croffles. The stew was laden with flavourful toppings of dumplings, spam, sausages, rice cakes and kimchi. I d also like to thank the service staff for being so amicable and friendly. The atmosphere and decor of the place was charming, with a themed section at the back, perfect for taking photos. I strongly recommend this restaurant, it is a stand out.
Food is super delicious! The tteokbokki was better than any other ones i ve had in Singapore and the croffles were creamy and tasted amazing. Service was also excellent, will definitely come again!

Authentic and delicious! Great service by the owner. We felt like we were being transported to Seoul! Perfect and will definitely visit again to try all the food in the menu! Especially Gimbap is the best
Really great service and good tteokbokki!

Second many of the reviews that the price is not worth it given 1. It s all carbs 2. Barely any flavour (ordered the seafood pot) 3. The sticky rice cakes, which are basically what I was there for, are way too soft and not chewy and overcooked. They didn t even have chili so I just had to swallow bland tasteless rice paste (not chewy enough to be called rice cakes) by itself. Especially given how many truly great Korean restaurants you have in the same neighbourhood, I would not recommend this one in good conscience

Tried the Wide Vermicelli with Fritters ($16.90) and it was a pretty scrumptious alternative to tteok-bokki which I just wasnt feeling that day. Unfortunately, waiting time was a tad long as they got my order wrong at first. My coworkers had their noodles and fried chicken dishes and everyone was overall pleased with the food here.
The owner is friendly, the food is plentiful and delicious!
It was so delicious and the owner was so kind!! Its exactly the same as what I eat in Korea haha.

Oreo croffle tasted amazing! One of the best croffle in Singapore. Freshly made and crispy (Might take awhile though). Definitely would recommend if you are looking for a Korean grade croffle,     Ordered Green Grape Ade is really refreshing :) Parking: Parallel Parking available in front of the shops
The owner was very friendly and the portions were generous and delicious!

I came here to eat tteokbokki last time, and it was so delicious that I came again! This time, I had Budae Jjigae, and it was a lot and really delicious. There were so many different ingredients, so it was really good! I ate until I was full   The owner was also very kind    Ill come again next time

It s the taste of Korea!! The owner is so kind and pretty haha. The atmosphere is comfortable and the service is good, including adjusting the spiciness, so I plan to visit again :) This is an amazing place that can feel the real Korean taste!!
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: !! :) This is an amazing place that can feel the real Korean taste!!

detailed_reviews.review_text: It tastes good. Typical instant rice cake taste? But I wonder if this price is right. As a Korean, it is a shame to buy it at an expensive price.
authentic korean food! would recommend getting the tteokbokki set for 2, comfort food vibes <3 portion is huge tho, so gotta pace yourself or just come with more people

Ordered a two pax Teokbokki meal ( spicy level 1) The portion is quite small for two pax, and lacking as compared to other Korean eateries in the area.. The ingredients provided are mainly carbs (diff shapes of Teokbokki and Maggie mee). There s only an egg, a few small slices of fish cake and 2 Mandus included in the meal.. Definitely not worth $30++ with this portion and ingredients..

Came because of TikTok but Honey chicken flavour was good, although for $16 the portion is really too small. Especially when compared to normal Korean restaurants this is too small. Ordered the TBK stew it was average. Also, probably the first Korean restaurant that DOES NOT serve free water or ban chan (sides). Honestly if the prices are typical Korean charges but the food are smaller in portion with the lack of frills provided then it s really nothing to shout about. Unlikely to return. Many better Korean restaurants to visit nearby

After eating spicy dakgalbi, I had Crofl and a glass of Einspänner for dessert.  The whipped cream on top of the coffee is delicious and makes me happy.  There are no photos of the tiramisu croutons because they are sliced so quickly. Photos are included in the event...
Yummy rose tteokbokki and good service. Only thing is ramen add on costs $5.50
Marshmallow chocolate crople is the best!
Authentic Korean restaurant that serves homely food that is good for big groups; both food and service are excellent.
Food was awesome. Especially the toppoki beef brisket stew and non spicy fishcake soup. Honey garlic chicken is so so and rather on the sweeter side.

We ordered a good for 2 pork cutlet tteokbokki but it was good for 3 people as well, original flavor, and half and half chicken. Really enjoyed it and we were full. Our seat was a little dark though haha, but ambiance was nice.
Been here probably 50+ times. Dukkbooki is always consistent and delicious. I recommend the original level. Best paring is with the rice balls  . Service is always wonderful as well!
Tteokbokki is delicious

Ordered a crispy chicken rose tteokbokki, a half-half chicken, a flying fish roe rice, a seaweed roll and two bottles of soju which was just nice for 5 of us. Tteokbokki was nice and chewy, and had a good variety of ingredients, but level 2 is really not spicy - would recommend to try level 3 instead. Chicken was quite disappointing for me because it seems to be frozen chicken bites and was quite fatty. My favourite was the flying fish roe rice which was really delicious! But could probably be replicated pretty easily at home haha. Had higher expectations and meal was not cheap, so 3/5

To be quite honest I went there with really high expectations, but it just tasted like bland soup tteokbokki. There was a bit of a smell at Chadol, but the quality of the meat was the same at Korean tteokbokki restaurants, so it didnt really matter. Although it looked delicious in the photo, I was really disappointed and just ate it without saying anything. In Korea, you can eat delicious and spicy Sinjeon Tteokbokki for 3,500 won, but here you dont even order anything and it doesnt taste that good, but it costs 67,000 won. It might be better to just buy the ingredients and cook it at home. When I saw the butter garlic fries, I thought of a youth café and ordered it right away!! So the moment I take a bite, huh..? How is this butter garlic? Its not the butter garlic fries we imagined, but the fries are a little dry, the sauce tastes like mustard, and theres garlic in between. Its a waste of money. Just go to McDonalds and get the fries. I went there thinking it would be better than two meals, but if you just go for two meals with unlimited refills, I recommend it because you can adjust the seasoning and eat as much as you want. Im really sorry, but I was very disappointed.

Went To Try This Right After My 2nd Disappointing Visit At Chicken Up@Buangkok For My Favourite Army Stew... Everything Looks Yummy On Their Menu & Their Food Quality & Servings Are Better Than e Others I Would Say...     Their Added Cheese Are Superb Especially If You Are A Cheesy Lover Like Me   However Their Toppoki Are Not As Chewy As What Ive Tried So Far From A Few Other Korean Restaurants... But Still... Ill Give Them A Higher Rating Coz Their Staff Service Are Excellent Too Whether On e Warmth Welcome, Approached Or Recommendations On Food Choices   Ill Definitely Be Back Again To Try Some Other Food On Their Menu Soon... Cheers~ Still Loving It...

Had a pleasant experience dining at Red Holic! Chanced upon this eatery as we were walking down Tanjong Pagar Road, looking for options. Decided to give this place a try as the menu looked interesting, and we weren t disappointed! Food was tasty and strong in flavour, we ended up getting more than we initially ordered. Staff were rather friendly and helpful, would probably give this place another go if we re in the area, considering how crowded it can get especially on the weekend! :)
Very impressed with their teokbokki! especially Rose flavour! The added cheese ties in nicely as well. Would recommend to give this little store a try :)
Small place but tasty authentic Korean food.  Lack varieties though.

Food was quite spicy but portions are really generous. One pot was enough to feed three people. Cheezy dog was also really nice as a side dish. To add, the place was also not crowded on a weekday afternoon. However, nothing extraordinary about the food unfortunately, but good for anyone looking for a hearty home-cooked Korean meal.

We dropped by recently for a tteokbokki fix and tried the chadol tteokbokki set, which includes chadolbagi (thin-sliced meat) in addition to several kinds of tteok, instant noodles, odeng, and a hard-boiled egg. It was all right but a little too soupy and far too sweet for me. Otherwise, it was okay. We also tried the seaweed rolls, which were okay. If you want water, you have to buy a bottle for $2. Not the end of the world but I felt like tap water ought to be on offer. Service was decent. The two people working out front when we went were both Korean, so no communication issues. They were friendly and helpful. They have a one-hour time limit on seating, but that s frankly plenty for a meal like this. They also offer aprons for those who want them to protect their clothes, which was a nice touch. All in all, not the best I ve had but not bad.
Yummy rose stew! Fries were ok

Had lunch here during a Sunday afternoon. I rarely eat Korean cuisine so I am not sure whether its authentic or not. Ordered beef brisket with level 2 spicy. Overall the taste is good for me. The portion can feed up to 3 pax, a bit too much for 2 persons. Quite full but a bit boring towards the end because all the ingredients are rice cake related and noodles. Great and friendly staff! Food served in a short period.
Very nice tteokbokki.. i will come again.
Honey Chicken was really good.

This was my second time visiting. Army stew for one person, butter garlic fries, and Korean fried chicken were ordered. $ Ramen/instant noodles, hotdog, spam luncheon meat, bacon, enoki mushroom, sausage, and cabbage/kimchi are served hot. (Bacon and luncheon meat are my favorites.) $ . The butter garlic fries were supplied with a pitiful sauce that differed from the illustrated menu pic. When we told them about it, they gave us more sauce on the side. (Excellent service recovery) $ . The boneless chicken was adequate but not exceptional. Its just regular fried chicken. $ FYI: The toilet is shared and very clean. Spacious

Tried the dakgalbi here which is really (really) good - very similar to those I ve had at home-run eateries in Korea. The seaweed rice balls were tasty too. Highly recommended for those. Flavours were on point especially the dokboki in the dakgalbi which had amazingly soft yet chewy texture  the kind that doesn t make your mouth hurt. Some other points tho - The drinks are pricey and they don t serve with ice unless you ask (even so you need to ask for extra servings of ice cos the qty is really little). You also need to ask for serviettes instead of easily accessing it at the table. Side dishes are also not served. Not sure if it s a diff in what we re used to at other Korean restaurants here but given the price levels charges, these points or lack thereof can come off as cheap? Understand business costs of course so wouldn t judge harshly on this and would return again anyway.

Firstly, the environment of the place is clean and comfy, even the toilet is super clean. We chose Crispy chicken rose tteokbokki, its creamy and sweet at the same time. And we top it up with cheese fall! But if we come back will definitely order level 3 spicy or above, as level 2 spicy is original not a hint of kick. Need add more spice to cover the sweet taste that overwhelms you after awhile. Overall will recommend cheese lovers and k food lovers to come over to come.
The most delicious tteokbokki!
Interesting eat that is nice.. I do like their pork cutlet n yam rice cake... if u like Korean tobbokki can try.. quite interesting..

I love tteokbokki so much in Korea that I searched hard and found this tteokbokki restaurant! I was looking forward to going and trying it, but there were so many different kinds and the seasoning was so delicious that I ate it to my stomach. I will be making regular reservations in the future!

Got the regular ttebokki for $28.80, I would say there s nothing special about it given the price. Taste wise, it wasn t fantastic either as it got really greasy and too thick and creamy for my liking after a while (a bit ni). Drinks were unusually pricey, coke for $3, peach juice for $4 and ice water for $2. Plus, we had to wait in the queue for 45mins! Overall, this experience wasn t great but there s definitely room for improvement!

We got the beef brisket combo! First few bites tasted really good, but when you re about halfway, the taste can get really gelat because the sauce is just one dimensional.  Hence, it would be the perfect portion for 3 pax, a little too much for 2. The saving grace was the fried fritters and seaweed rice balls  they add crunch and texture to the whole dish which was just chewy throughout. Teokkbokki was the perfect chewiness for me and didn t taste like those frozen ones. Though the cabbage in the stew was way too little. Sauce dried up rather quickly over the stove so we requested to add more but the staff said no. Service wasn t great at all.
The ricecake is stale
good food with good service.

i tried their crispy chicken rose army stew with a friend and it was amazing!!! certainly really delicious   the noodles wasn t soggy, the chicken was crispy and the soup was yummy! service is also really good. i ll definitely come back here again!! update : i ve recently came back and tried the army stew (1 pax) with carbonara ! it is okay, i felt that the carbonara taste was pretty mild. overall, still prefer the rose version.
Great food and ambience! Friendly staff :) Quite big portion!
Food was not bad! Though I think they are a little short of staff and lucky it wasnt too crowded

Must try DakGalBi here! Taste really same in korea! Shop owner and chef are korean, thats why real korean taste! I was so long never back to korea,so miss DakGalBi  but now I can go there eat with a lot cheese  its super yummy

Great service from 2 Korean waitress here. But food for me is so so. I was very curious taste of rose teokpokki so I ordered 1 big bowl of rose teokpokki with beef brisket and added on fen hao zi and cheese fall. The taste was very similar to Samyang carbonara and level 2 spiciness was too mild and greasy for me. I saw many reviews said cheese fall was a must try. In the end we cant finish and I think I can do this myself at home with very low cost. Total it cost me $65.55 included 1 bottle of mineral water. The sauce could be better and it doesnt stand out. Perhaps my expectation is little bit too high.

this place was generally okay. cheese fall is a must-get if youre there, otherwise the food tastes mostly like any other army stews / dakgalbi. found the sauce a bit too sweet for my liking. cheese fall added a lot of flavours to the chicken, albeit a little steep in pricing ($8.90 per fall). also got the sides but tastes pretty normal as well. the rice cakes however, were pretty good - unlike some which are too hard or too mushy, the rice cakes here were done nicely, and with a variety as well. do note that they dont serve water or side dishes here, unlike other korean food joints.

Everything was good! Service was prompt as well. We ordered the rice cake set, fishcake soup, mixed fried items set B and honey chicken. Every single dish was great, would come again and hopefully try their soondae:)
Tteokbokki is so delicious
Decent street food-style dishes. Pretty stiff and curt service though. And dont try to celebrate a birthday cos the staff wont let you cut a cake there its considered outside food.
we ordered rose flavour but came carbonara, it was a bit too gelat after awhile. the chicken wings is fantastic 5/5.
No frills kind of korean place. Very casual. Ordered the dakgalbi which was too saucy and watery in my opinion but tasted pretty decent! Portion was big so it was pretty valued for money.

Its just tteokbokki soup. This is the state before taking out the instant tteokbokki and pouring water into it and boiling it. The workers are not friendly at all. People say,  It usually comes out like this with a lot of water.  I wonder if you ve never tried tteokbokki. It s a taste that I can t find an answer to. Absolutely not recommended. The reason it has 3.9 stars is probably because it was built up when the previous boss was there. If youre going to eat tteokbokki, go for two meals instead.
The worst Tteokbokki i have ever had. Soup was so dilute, tasted like chili powder soup. Staff was also rude. They seemed uninterested to work. Dont waste your money.
Too slow to prepare

Ordered their rose sauce, filling enugh for 3 pax. It s not bad! Be prepared for a lot of carbs hahaha also there s tang hun! Hahaha mala lovers would know this. Total: $75 for 3 pax with 2 soju and 1 bottle of Dasani at $1.

didnt take any pictures but i went with my girl friends and we ordered the tteokbokki carbonara base with chicken set! it was just nice for the 3 of us and it tasted great, go ahead and try with the normal bases cos i think it s nice too!! we just didnt choose it because my friend cant take anything thats even a lil spicy.
Do you think this is worth 15 SGD? And the owner always disrespect customers  order, and interlope on people enforcing to order more.

Unbelievably rude staff, not reasonable price considering food s quality and taste. Not recommend this place. lThis place has ridiculously rude staff. Even the taste of tteokbokki is not that good. I went there with great expectations, but I was only disappointed. It wouldnt have been this unpleasant if it werent for the taste, but I have absolutely no intention of visiting again due to the rude staff. You dont have to be polite to customers, but do the basics.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Unbelievably rude staff, not reasonable price considering food s quality and taste. Not recommend this place. l                       .                 .                    .                         ,                          . .

detailed_reviews.review_text: Staff are Korean but they could not speak English, having tough time. As for the foodie, i think other restaurants out there are far better.
Soso food. Couldve given the choice for customer to customise the ingredients in the pot  because there was too much rice cakes lol

Super yummy Korean street food with a drool worthy cheese waterfall you can add on top of your dish. Must get! Came back a second time and the food quality was still amazing. Would recommend ordering the beef brisket tteokbokki, enough to feed 3 pax. Love the variety of the ingredients, especially the special sweet potato tteok. Side dishes are all so tasty, you must try the fried fish cake. My friends have had the corn dog, fries and fried dumplings (mandu), and all seemed great. Food is also quite value for money, costing us under $30 per pax each time.
Delicious, big portion for 3, went with colleagues.

Place is small but very cozy! Came in the afternoon around 1pm. Ambience wise nice korean music but, it may have been loud to some! Pretty decorations. Staff helped to stir the tteokbokki and for us which was nice! Had the chicken tteokbokki and butter garlic fries! Taste wise 8/10. Price wise may be a little pricey but the food and environment isn t too bad!
Delicious tteokbokki restaurant
Nice food and nice service, it s better than most of Korea stew I have had.
Not recommended. Mediocre food and staff
Tiny outfit along Tanjong Pagar Road. The tteokbokki stew is almost comparable to the ones I had in Seoul.

I had it delivered and it was great!! Next time, Im going to try the spicy flavor. They packaged the ramen noodles separately to prevent them from getting soggy, and I didnt know they came with steamed egg as well   It tastes like Korean tteokbokki, everyone.

Really, if possible, it would be much better to wait until it opens later and eat at the store instead of ordering delivery. The portion was very small, the tteokbokki had no taste and was very bland, and the odeng soup was a complete mess. I think its too insincere to say its delivery.

Maybe its because I had high expectations after hearing that it was similar to Young Mans Coffee Shop... but it wasnt that good. I dont know if its not as good compared to Youth Coffee Shop, but its not as good compared to regular tteokbokki restaurants... Its cheaper and more delicious to go here for two meals at Olppa. I think it would be better to eat two meals of Singapore Tteokbokki.
Super authentic Korean food, recommend the rosé cream stew!
Good quality Korean food
Good tasty Korean food and snack in Singapore

Redholic was a walk down memory lane after my visit to Seoul earlier this year. Their recreation of authentic Korean street food served in their outlet in Tanjong Pagar, it s well worth a visit. Whether it s the tasty fish cake or the spicy tteokbokki, most Koreans will feel at home here.

Food is quite pricey, but what do you expect when its the Tanjong Pagar area? :) Food was enjoyable to a certain extent; I came especially for the cheese tteokbokki but went away feeling overwhelmed by the sheer amount of melted cheese that soon became tough and rubbery in the watery tteokbokki stew. The rest of the tteokbokki was delicious though. I became full quite soon enough. So I think its suffice to say that a single cheesy tteokbokki set will fill one up easily enough. I think I picked the wrong sides, found the butter garlic fries a bit too intense (and not necessarily in the best way). Mozzarella sticks were delicious and piping hot. My partner commented that the ramyeon was yummy, but not befitting of the price. We were served big thick slices of yellow pickled radish and given a jug of icy water. Service was a bit meh. The lone, bespectacled  server we had that day was awfully quiet, almost to the point of being aloof and seemed rather shy, so we had to be louder, and called him several times to get his attention. He forgot the drink we ordered as well. But he wasnt rude, so Ill warrant a guess that he isnt too familiar with the job yet..? Its not bad a place if you have cash to splurge and youre familiar enough with Red Holic to know what you want.

I really wanted to eat tteokbokki, so I went to Tanjongpaga Kkuyeokkku Station and ate it. Its on the first floor. I was expecting a youth cafe and took just one bite, but it was better than I expected, huh..? I was a little embarrassed. Still, its a bit odd... Its chewy... But I dont know why they give me the oden. Its a dish made by boiling several pieces and then heating them up... Its so hard...~

Booking on their Facebook page was read but not confirmed. Arrived at place and was told to wait for 15 minutes. Waited for half an hour and the staff didnt even bothered to inform us that the wait will be delayed. The staff was rude when we asked about the waiting time.
All the foods are great here!! If you are ddeokbokki lover, this place is a must visit!

It was my first time eating Chadol Tteokbokki in a country other than Korea, so I liked it and it was delicious. I ate it with the original sauce at level 2 spiciness, but it was a bit sweet and salty! Next time, I will try it in 3 stages.
Good food and a lot of drinks. Staff friendly but dont understand everything. That is fun :)

Long queue during Friday evening, so do expect some waiting. Not many options in the menu but its main is tteokbokki, which is the specialty. Mini tteokbokki with crispy chicken in original flavour is nice. Korean sausage served with liver/kidney (I assumed) was good but it quite pricey with the portion given.

Nice cosy ambience with great food. The  serving for tteokbokki is really generous in terms of portion and ingredients. Nice and spicy but it was a tad too sweet for me. Great friendly service too. Will definitely return for more.

Went there for their army stew, but was quite disappointed. All the ingredients inside are carb-rich and starchy which made me feel nauseated after a while (Maggi noodle, glass noodle, potato starch noodle, extremely generous amount of rice cakes, dumplings with flour starch fillings?) The only meat was just a small pork cutlet for two persons to share, not to mention the absence of luncheon meat, sausages, crabsticks etc. Variety of vegetables is also very limited. It would be good to add more variety into the stew and if the portion of each ingredient can be better balanced. Nevertheless, staff service is very good! If the chopsticks could be changed to those authentic korean metal ones, instead of those plastic kopitiam chopsticks, i think the whole feel might be improved significantly.

Super yummy food, comparable to what I had in Korea! Our reservation fell through when we were there, but the owner was really nice and apologetic and gave us some free drinks and food. Really wonderful experience all around, will definitely be back.
We had fun with the cheese that is super stretchy. hahaa. Good food and service.
Have a brisket meal. It s delicious.
Friendly owner, nice spicy food

Spicy food! Pricing around ($10++), went during lunch. Got different levels of spicy-ness so choose wisely! I love their odeng. It is really great. I would say it taste better than though i had in Korea.
Great soju promo, 3 bottles for $40
Its delicious, recommended ~ If youre curious, give it a try....
Very authentic tteokbbokki! Highly recommend :)  the fried rice at the end is also a must!
Awesome food, nice and friendly staff and chill ambience
The tteokbokki seemed a bit salty, but the brisket was also delicious and good. I want to go there with a lot of people and try other menu items.
Good foood!
it is delicious
Great Korean food and booze
I had a sore throat so asked for sweet instead of spicy. They gave me spicy food...I only went here because there were good reviews but very disappointed.
Spicy challenge is very challenging! For 1 person 20minutes and 2 people 12 minutes. We could not finish it..
The tteokbokki at this restaurant is the best. I go often and the service is great!
Its delicious haha
This restaurant has the genuine ambience and taste in Korea. Not like other restaurants selling every Korean food they can. Love the food! Def gonna visit again!

Tried the tteokbokki and the taste was great! Will definitely come back again. It was wallet friendly and also the staffs were pretty and handsome. Also kind as well. Mandu was affordable as well. Good!
Looking for awesome tteokboki, this place aint bad. Would come back again.

We went on a Tuesday afternoon(about 1:45pm) and the place was almost empty. I think the problem with eating just tteokbokki as a main course is that it gets sickening after awhile. We got the tteokbokki pot with beef($28+) and we also added the cheese waterfall for an additional $4. The portions were quite generous and I think 2-3 people could share it. The sauce was way too sweet for our liking but the ricecakes and other toppings were nice. Note that there is a lot of chewing involved. We also ordered the giant dumplings($1.80 each) - the meat dumpling was not bad, while the kimchi dumpling was a tad too hot/spicy. Oh yes, and the place was too warm!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi, Thank you for your support! As for the Taste, We improved much more after customer feed backs and for the warmth, we have installed a new cassette Air-con. We hope you come back again!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Waited more than 30mins before realising that we had to write our names on the waiting list which shouldnt have been placed inside the restaurant if the restaurant wanted people to see it. No one came out to attend to us the entire duration while we queued. Only when I went in to ask did the waitress tell me they are going according waiting list. Wasted an hour queuing for nothing. Bad service, will not recommend.
Best teokkbokki     in Sing! Randomly went in for dumplings (which were amazing) and found a gem

The food is delicious~~ Tteokbokki is delicious, but fried squid and hotteok dumplings are also delicious :) It seems to be run by a Korean male owner, and perhaps thats why it tastes exactly like Korean instant rice cake. suggestion!!
